-- Shiv-Vani Oil & Gas Gains in Mumbai Trading on Plan to Borrow $95 Million
-- John Chacko
-- 2010-07-09T03:41:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-09/shiv-vani-oil-gas-gains-in-mumbai-trading-on-plan-to-borrow-95-million.html

          
          
             Shiv-Vani Oil & Gas Exploration
Services Ltd. gained in Mumbai trading after the exploration
company said it plans to borrow as much as $95 million selling
convertible bonds.  
 The stock gained 3.5 percent to 472 rupees at 9:07 a.m.
local time after surging as much as 8.3 percent.  
          
          


  


        